The source currently uses the following style:

```
if (x)
    y;
else
    z;

if (x)
    y;
else {
    z;
    z;
}
```

I'd prefer linux kernel style:

```
if (x)
    y;
else
    z;

if (x) {
    y;
} else {
    z;
    z;
}
```

When we're talking about a source of bugs with if statements, I think this is worse (and I've seen it several places in the codebase):

```
if (a)
  do_something();
if (b)
  do_something_else();
else
  do_another();
```

The problem here is a missing blank line after the first if. It easily looks like `if (b)` is an `else if (b)`
